body:
@jzgithub1 you have a checkstyle violation.  Follow through the details of the travis-ci build or go directly to https://travis-ci.org/apache/accumulo/jobs/493247193.

Consider rebase -i to clean up the commits and make one concise commit message.

Also remove the * import, I'll put a comment on the line

> The main problem isn't the infinite set of log messages... the main problem is that the test enters some failure state, and never exits that state. Yes, suppressing the log message will help not fill up disk... but it's also not a solution to the underlying problem of the test never realizing it's in a failure state and continuing forever.

From the error message it looks like the `servers` variable is not getting populated and is an empty list. I bet there is a timing issue and could be fixed with retries.

```
2018-08-13 17:44:37,310 [test.TransportCachingIT] WARN : Failed to obtain transport to []
```

The following code should probably be wrapped in a while loop that repeats (with a 100ms sleep each time) until `servers` is not empty.  There could be a check that just fails the test if this code is retried like 100 times and servers is still empty.

```
    ArrayList<ThriftTransportKey> servers = new ArrayList<>();
      for (String tserver : children) {
        String path = zkRoot + Constants.ZTSERVERS + "/" + tserver;
        byte[] data = ZooUtil.getLockData(zc, path);
        if (data != null) {
          String strData = new String(data, UTF_8);
          if (!strData.equals("master"))
            servers.add(new ThriftTransportKey(
                new ServerServices(strData).getAddress(Service.TSERV_CLIENT), rpcTimeout, context));
        }
      }
```
